# i18n (next-intl) Patterns

## 1. Translation Files
- All language files go in `src/i18n/locales/{lang}.json`.
- JSON structure is flat with dot-notation keys (e.g. "auth.login").

## 2. Translation Usage in Code
- Use the `useTranslations` hook from `next-intl`.
- Get a translation function by namespace.
- Never hardcode UI textâ€”always use message IDs.

```typescript
import { useTranslations } from "next-intl";
const t = useTranslations("auth");
<Button>{t("login")}</Button>
```

## 3. Top-Level Provider
- At app root/layout include NextIntlProvider (see next-intl docs for usage).

## 4. Example en.json
```json
{
  "auth.login": "Login",
  "auth.signup": "Sign Up",
  "movie.title": "Title"
}
```
